\n\\nI’m thinking about how the Doxia module might only be suitable for typical minimal setups. I should check the upstream DefaultSiteRendererTest to understand how it's utilizing various file formats. It's crucial to ensure everything's aligned and that I'm using the right configurations. By inspecting these details, I’m hoping to identify any necessary adjustments or optimizations. I wonder how it all connects together and if I might find something interesting to tweak.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_l8MhLzkcK2L9LYXdMteneXme|fc_032f3c2c281324f9016a3fba5c6b3c8190a2c84f87f7cad58e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurl='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apache/maven-doxia-sitetools/doxia-sitetools-2.0.0/doxia-site-renderer/src/test/java/org/apache/maven/doxia/siterenderer/DefaultSiteRendererTest.java'\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15).read().decode()\nfor pat in ['apt','xdoc','fml','locateDocumentFiles','renderDocument','copyResources','createContextForSkin']:\n print('\\n--', pat)\n for m in re.finditer(pat, data):\n  s=max(0,m.start()-250); e=min(len(data),m.end()+350)\n  print(data[s:e].replace('\\n',' ')[:900])\n  break\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2816, "output": 742, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34278, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782561358853, "responseId": "resp_032f3c2c281324f9016a3fba4f576881908c28dbda662d9f66"}}
